d Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William Tailboys was born in 1315, in Northumberland, England, United Kingdom, his father, LUCAS TALIBOYS, was 58 and his mother, Alice Chartney, was 52. He married Margaret Egglescliffe in 1322, in Northumberland, England. They were the parents of at least 3 sons. He died on 20 October 1365, at the age of 50."},"et":{"1285 age 30-1315–20 October 1365":"1315–20. oktoober 1365","1286–Female":"1286–Surnud","1286–Male":"1286–Surnud","1288–Male":"1288–Surnud","1308–Female":"1308–Surnud","1315–1365":"1315–1365","1299–Female":"1299–Surnud","1335–1369":"1335–1369","1337–Male":"1337–Surnud","1339–Male":"1339–Surnud","1258–1316":"1258–1316","1264–Female":"1264–Surnud","1285 age 30-1315":"1315","1264":"1264","1286":"1286","Abt 1335":"umbes 1335","1316":"1316","20 October 1365":"20. oktoober 1365","Abt 1284":"umbes 1284","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1369":"1369","1258":"1258","1335":"1335","1322":"1322","about 1339":"umbes 1339","1299":"1299","1365":"1365","1288":"1288","about 1337":"umbes 1337","1308":"1308","1339":"1339",", Northumberland, England":"Northumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Northumberland, England":"Northumberland, England","Hepple, Northumberland, England":"Hepple, Northumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1285 age 30-1315–20 October 1365":"1315–20. lokakuuta 